extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

Tuple representation in Java.


A tuple is an immutable, expandable and ordered data type, that can hold objects of different types:
  • You can't change a specific Tuple by addition or removal of elements, only form new ones.
  • Items are stored in order of addition: that means that if you add a String object after a Number object (for example), the former's index will be lower than the latter's.
Since:
2.0.0
Author:
Nuno Pereira
